title: Fitzpatrick rallies East Brunswick football to victory
text:

East Brunswick 24, Marlboro 15: Almaliek Fitzpatrick had a stellar all-around game for the Bears including two third-quarter touchdowns that helped East Brunswick pull away for a win over a rebuilding Shore Conference program. 
Fitzpatrick caught five passes for 68 yards and rushed four times for 35 yards. He also had eight tackles, three passes defended and an interception. 
After Marlboro took a 7-0 lead on a 70-yard touchdown pass, Alex Boyko booted a 25-yard field goal in the first quarter, trimming the gap to four points. 
East Brunswick (3-3) took the lead for good minutes later on Kyle Wiggins’ 15-yard touchdown run. 
Fitzpatrick caught a 27-yard scoring strike from James Schuld and scored on a 15-yard run – both in the third quarter – as the Bears built a 24-7 lead. 
Marlboro closed out the scoring with a 30-yard touchdown run in the final stanza. 
The loss was the 18th in a row for Marlboro (0-6). Read or Share this story: http://mycj.co/1S1O8Hy TOP VIDEOS
